                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-531" type="given" value="ROBERT TYRRELL"></interp>ROBERT TYRRELL READ</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. William Ward, a salesman, in Gray's Inn-lane. On the 9th of July, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner stoop down and take a pair of boots from a box under the window, outside the shop—he put them under his coat, and went about two yards—I followed, took hold of him, and took them from under his coat—he did not say anything, but began to wring my ears—the officer came and took him—these are the boots—they are my master's.</p>
